==English==

===Noun===
'''siding'''
# The [[material]] which covers and protects the [[side]]s of a [[house]] or other [[building]].
#:''Ugh.  If there's one thing I can't stand it's cheesy vinyl siding.''
# {{cattag|railroading}} A second, relatively short length of [[track]] just to the side of a [[railroad]] track, joined to the main track by [[switch]]es at one or both ends, used either for unloading freight or to allow two trains to pass.

===Verb===
'''siding'''
# Participle of [[side|to side]].
#:''Whenever he hears an argument, he can't help '''siding''' with one party or the other.''